titleInfo.title: USA v. Beckstrom et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER as to defendant Cory Beckstrom (1). The motion for discovery and extension of the pretrial motion deadline (Filing No. 36) is granted. The government shall provide Beckstrom with such recordings or provide an explanation why such recordings do not exist or set forth the date when such recordings may have already been produced to the defendant. A certificate of the delivery of such discovery or government's declaration shall be filed on or before July 20, 2012. Thereafter, Beckstrom shall have until August 10, 2012, in which to file any pretrial motions. Pretrial Motion Deadline set for 8/10/2012. Ordered by Magistrate Judge Thomas D. Thalken. (GJG)

titleInfo.title: USA v. Beckstrom et al
titleInfo.subTitle: PRELIMINARY ORDER OF FORFEITURE as to defendant Cory Beckstrom (1). The United States's Motion for Issuance of Preliminary Order of Forfeiture, filing 89 is hereby sustained. Based upon the Forfeiture Allegation of the Indictment and the Defendant's plea of guilty, the United States is hereby authorized to seize the $999 and $1,920 in United States currency. Upon adjudication of all third-party interests, this Court will enter a Final Order of Forfeiture pursuant to 21 U.S.C. section 853(n), in which all interests will be addressed. Ordered by Chief Judge Laurie Smith Camp. (1 Certified copy to USM)(GJG)
